<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 20 at 3:41AM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...ENHANCED FIRE DANGER THIS AFTERNOON...
Very dry air and gusty winds will lead to increased fire danger
through this evening. Relative humidity values will drop between
20 to 30 percent with wind gusts between 20 and 30 mph this
afternoon. These conditions will combine with dry brush, grasses,
and other fuels to increase fire danger across the region.
Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities on whether
you can burn today. Use extreme caution when burning as fires may
get out of hand quickly under these conditions.</description>
